<p>After <a href="https://christiantietze.de/posts/2023/01/use-sf-pro-for-sf-symbols-everywhere-in-emacs/">discovering how to use SF Symbols in Emacs on Mac</a>, folks on Reddit shared links where Josh Caswell (known by his handle “woolsweater”) did stuff like this ages ago.</p>

<figure><a href="https://christiantietze.de/posts/2023/01/woolsweater-s-sf-symbols-modeline/woolsweater-code.png"><img alt="" src="https://christiantietze.de/posts/2023/01/woolsweater-s-sf-symbols-modeline/woolsweater-code.png" /></a><figcaption>This is how the SF Symbol glyphs render if you can actually see them. I.e, outside the browser's code preview.</figcaption></figure>

<p>Check out his DOOM Emacs compatible, <code>doom-modeline</code> based SF Symbols iconification in <a href="https://git.sr.ht/~woolsweater/.emacs.d/tree/b84f811fa36044940308bd0665e0516d7840ba6d/item/modules/sfsymbols-modeline.el">sfsymbols-modeline.el</a>.</p>
